As your town or nation grows you might find you building needs growing aswell! Here at research and development we have discovered loads of new ways to spruce up those government buildings!

§4Unlocks Chisels and Bits, Chisel, Architecture Craft

All great civilizations have to start somewhere!

§F§4Unlocks Iron Manipulation

Normal Minecraft tools are great, but you're town isn't going to flourish with basic iron tools! You gotta step up your game!

§4Unlocks Tinker's Construct

If you little settlement is ever going to grow into a thriving nation you're gonna need to get steel. Most machines later require steel so creating steel and stockpiling it is a good idea.

§4Unlocks Steel and Early Guns

With all the steel you know have been creating you can research how to heat up water to create steam. Big boilers will allow the creation of steam while pipes can be used to move the gas to various early machines.

§4Unlocks Boilers, Steam, and the Hand Cannon

This tech is a little all over the place, and I'm not really sure what I want to do with it, so I'm removing all cost except for the tool forge, so this tech won't gate anyones progress, since it's pretty WIP.

Having more options to choose from when it comes to food can have many benefits. Always eat a varied diet to get the nutrients you need from other foods.

§4Unlocks Pam's Harvest Craft Foods

Steam is great and all, but it would be much cooler if you didn't have waste your coal on heating water and instead could use the coal to directly create power! Also vehicles, combustion engines brings vehicles too. Almost forgot...

§4Unlocks Coal Generators and Basic Vehicles

Coal is great but you can't run vehicles and generators off nothing but coal. If you were to somehow take that large amount of crude oil thats in the ground and turn it into fuel, then your town might just be able to turn into a thriving city!

§5§4Unlocks Oil Processing and Refining and Vehicles

With ore veins further away from each other you might need to use trains to move ore and other materials across long distances. With steam locomotives you can transfer tons of items without needing long pipe systems. They're also great for getting around!

§4Unlocks Steam Locomotives

With your growing town you might have people start to notice your growth, you then might need to defend your town in the event another town tries to take what you worked hard to create!

§4Unlocks Techguns

If you have multiple towns in your nation you might need to travel to your different towns. One method of doing this is through flight! Have your researchers develop the basics to flying so you can fly through the air. Who knows maybe one day you can turn them into weapons.

§4Unlocks Basic Planes

You should always stay on alert, you never know who might be trying to invade you at any moment. What if you could make big bombs to discourage any invasions? That would be cool.

§4Begins the Research Towards Nuclear Energy and Weapons, gives tier 1 ICBMs

This uranium stuff is cool but it seems to be pretty unstable. So let's try to use it for power generation! With all this heat we can generate power with ease!

§4Unlocks Nuclearcraft and Progresses Research Towards Nuclear Weapons. Also unlocks advanced generators if you're into that.

As more technology gets invented more automation can be done. With computers, code can be written to perform automation with ease! If you're not into coding you can throw computers in your vehicles and your weapons to make better ones.

§4Unlocks Computers

If you would like to become a researcher for your town reach out to the mayor for the position.

As a researcher you gain access to the tech tree, and have the ability to advanced the technology of the town alongside the mayor and other researchers. Work together to develop research in the direction your mayor thinks is most valuable.

§4Note: If this quest doesn't complete for you after receiving the stage, try to relogin to the server.

I really hope these weapons never have to be used. This would have the potential to destroy whole towns! Moose Co recommends you use your newfound weapons only in emergencies!

§4Progresses Research Towards Nuclear Weapons

Wouldn't it be crazy if people could teleport? Sorry that was a weird thing to ask.

§4Unlocks Portality and EnderIO
The future is now

The mail system allows players to send and receive messages, even while offline. The most important usage of this system revolves around inviting players to a municipality. All players should setup a mailbox so mail addressed to you always arrives properly.

§9To setup a mailbox, place a sign anywhere with the following text:
§6[st-mailbox]
player
<player-name>

§rThis sign will now act as your mailbox. A number at the bottom of the sign represents how much mail you have, and assuming you have mail, you can right click on the sign to open the GUI.

§9To read mail, hold it and your hand and use:
§6/st-mail read

§9To send mail to other players use:
§6/st-mail send <receiver> <msg...>

Burning fossil fuels can make pollution, so we can generate power through cleaner means to reduce emissions.

§4Unlocks Solar Panels and other clean energy sources

Ok so after a bit more research we've discovered that planes can be even better! So we threw some better engines and some computers in there, along with seats, lots of seats. Actually the R&D team may have too many seats at this point... Maybe we can figure out how to make even bigger planes which more seats? Eh who knows.

§4Unlocks Advanced Planes

Hey we were actually able to fine a use for all of those seats! We've created planes that can transport tons of people and tons of cargo! Also we even figured out a few random vehicles and planes aswell!

§4Unlocks More Advanced Planes

Now that we know how computers work we can use computers and server so store items! At least I think that's how it works. The R&D breifing wasn't very indepth.

§4Unlocks Applied Energistics 2

Hello and welcome to Project Towny! A modpack focused on establishing towns, creating governments, declaring wars, initiating nuclear armageddon, annihilating opponents, making peace, and more! This quick questline will teach you the basics of the modpack, and get you started on making and running your very on town!

At the beginning of the pack you don't have many mods available to you. Researching all of these things will take time and money. Of course, time is money, so you’re just going to need a whole lotta cold, hard, pixelated cash. You can get this sweet sweet moolah by fulfilling orders through the bounty board. The mayor of a town will use that money to purchase new technology for the town, containing the distilled knowledge of each era. 

§4Once your town researches a new technology, simply run the command §6/research sync §r§4to add all techs from the town to your player. Run this from time to time to catch up with anything researched while you're not around!

§4§0§1§2§3§4§5§6§7§8§rMayors and researchers are in charge of research and development. By setting up towns and collecting taxes from citizens, mayor's will have more money to fund R&

Let's say you're the one that's in charge of creating the town and leading it into greatness! You're gonna need to know the basics of town creation!

Create a Municipality (Town) - Requires $400
§2/mun create <townname>
§rGets information about the district you're standing in
§2/dis info
§rOpens a chunk claiming GUI for that district - Requires §2§r$25 per chunk
§2/ck claim <district-id>
§rInvites a player to your Municipality
§2/mun invite <playername>
§rGets information about the Municipality you're standing in
§2/mun info

§rA more detailed explaination can be found in the Mayoral Duties Questline.

§4If you're playing single player then this will not apply to you.

If you're the mayor or a citizen that pays taxes you're are gonna need to know how money works.

There are two types of currency.
§2Physical Money
§4Digital Money

§r§2Physical money is the physical bills you get from completing bounties in the bounty board. Physical money can be used to trade between players and fund research.

§l§l§l§r§4Digital Money is the money you get from converting Physical Money via an ATM. Digital money is the money collected from taxes and spent on town and nation costs. Don't ignore this or you might be kicked out of a town for not having enough money in your account to pay taxes!

§1§6Spawn contains a central bank that allows you to transfer money between the two types of currency. It's a good idea to keep most of your money in the digital form, as it's safe from being stolen or lost. If you're tired of going to spawn to exchange your money you can ask your mayor to purchase an ATM for the town.

Now that you're ready to become mayor let's begin. To unlock the Mayoral Duties Questline run the command /diplomacy mayor, to give yourself the "mayor" gamestage.

§4Note: You must be the mayor of a municipality to be able to run the command, if that wasn't obvious.

Other Note: If this quest doesn't complete for you after running the command, try to relogin to the server.

If you're here this means that you are not the mayor of a town and are instead a citizen of a town. While the mayor is doing all the work managing the town you can still help better the town by providing services that benefit the town. 

Create factories to produce goods to improve your town's production and wealth, build up town infrustructure like roads and utilities to aid other players in their goals, create a mining company to provide your town with large quantities of resources, become a town builder and build up your town to make it look the best is possibly can, or just sit around and watch everything grow around you. As a citizen you can play however you want to play!

It's up to the mayor on how they handle research but if you don't like how they're handling it, you can stage an uprising against the mayor and bring the town to the ground! 

Or just simply leave the town for another one if that's more your style...

Begin your nations space race by constructing satellites and gathering data from space. You wouldn't want to send your brave citizens into the unknown without having a understanding of where they're heading right?

§4During this stage your nation should build the starter space infrastructure and launch satellites to gather distance, composition, and mass data.

To complete this stage, launch a distance satellite, a composition satellite, and a mass satellite, and collect 5000 data of each type. (You can also launch more than one to speed this up)

After building your nations satellite network and collecting data, you now have a decent enough understanding to being to put a man on the moon.

§4During this stage your nation should reach the moon, and uncover the new materials awaiting.

To complete this stage, launch a player to the moon, and come back with samples from the surface. To unlock the next stage, atomic research must be complete!

Now that your nation has it's space station up in the sky, you can begin to research more advanced space technology. Starting with the first more advanced tech, asteroid mining!

§4During this stage your nation should build up the needed infrastructure to begin mining asteroids.

To complete this stage, mine an ore only found in asteroids.

Congrats! Your nation has reached the end of the line in advanced rocketry. Feel free to screw around and discover all the new planets and their resources that I made for this modpack.

When 0.7 releases I'll probably include more reason to use this advanced technology, like experiments and specific resources you need from other planets, but for now just explore the cool ones I've made. Some have lots of resources, and some are even pretty special. Happy space travels!

After touching down on the surface of the moon, your nations space knowledge should be advanced enough to get your nations very own space station in the sky.

§4During this stage your nation should build a space station, capable of performing experiments.

To complete this stage, launch a space station and construct a Dilithium Reaction Chamber to create Dilithium Crystals from lithium dust, and lots of power.

The Dilithium Reaction Chamber requires a microgravity environment, meaning the machine will only work on space stations. 

Researching this tech will allow you to continue forward past rocketry in the main tech tree.

Managing the research of a town all on your own is hard work. Luckily for you Moose Co has created our very on research system to make your life just a little easier! No longer do you have to soley manage all technology. Now you can appoint players in your municipality as researchers to work with you on the tech tree. Now all you have to do is manage the budget!

Our research system works as follows:

Mayors appoint town researchers with §2/research add <player>§r

When a researcher unlocks a new technology that technology will be added to the town research pool.

Once a new technology is in the research pool, players can use §2/research sync§r to collect the research from the town's research pool.

The questbook tech tree will automatically update when a new technology is collected from the town's research pool, allowing other researchers to move forward in the tree.

You can remove a researcher from the town with §2/research remove <player>§r, however this player will still have access to the tech tree, just without the ability to add technology to the town's research pool. If possible only appoint a researcher if you're sure you want them to be one for the lifespan of your town.

Lists all currently appointed town researchers
§2/research list

Little rafts can get small things around but what about larger scale boats? With the recent invention of the helm you can make huge boats to haul freight, explore the seas, or just to relax on. Also the move, I think that was pretty clear though.

§4Unlocks Davincis Vessels

With computers we can begin to explore the world beyond earth. Gather data, visit other planets, and discover new materials to advance your technology.

§4Unlocks Space Tech Tree

To continue past this tech on the tech tree, reach Space Station Research in the rocketry tech tree.

In Project Towny all ores are far apart from each other. They’re all bunched up in massive veins. You can find these all these veins by traversing the surface of the world! By simply walking around, you’ll find surface samples, hinting at a greater bounty below. By digging down from these surface samples, you’ll find great deposits of that respective ore, ripe for the taking. Some ores spawn only in certain biomes, and they’re all under different names, so to make things simpler, we’ve given you the Geolosys Field Manual, for all your prospecting needs!

§3§2§4§6§7§7§6§9§4Some are even on different planets. So finding a deposit and setting up a method of transport of getting to that deposit is pretty important.

§d§1§9§4FYI osmium is on the moon... Good luck!

Each food has a certain food group it is apart of. This means you need to have a varied diet. The higher all your food groups are the better buffs you will get, while the neglecting your food groups will result in debuffs.

The world has seasons, each season has different stats and such. Depending on the season the world and weather might look different. Also crops don't grow in certain seasons so it's a good idea to stock up on important crops that you'll be needing.

The States mod is a complex land claiming mod used to claim land for your towns and nations.

States has 4 different "Levels" of land claiming:
Chunks -> Districts -> Municipalities -> States

Chunks: Basic Minecraft 16x16 block areas. The amount of chunks you can claim is determined by how many citizens are living in your Municipality. Costs $25 per chunk to claim.

Districts: Districts are made up of chunks. The amount of districts you can create is determined by how many chunks you have claimed for your Municipality. Costs $100 to make a new district.

Municipalities: Municipalities are made up of districts. Think of Municipalities as towns. This is what you are a mayor of. Municipalities are the most important type of land claiming in Project Towny. Costs $400 to make a Municipality.

States: States are made up of Municipalities. Think of States as Nations, that nation is made up of towns. States are the highest level of claiming currently available in the States mod.

Unions: Unions are made up of States, Unions do not exist at this time, but if you want to make Unions a reality I would talk to the developer of the States mod, possibly if enough people are interested he may work on the mod. Unions would truly be "Nations" or groups of allies, kinda like the United States, but at this time States are the highest you can do.

Chunks are the most basic unit in the States mod. Chunks are made up of an area of 16x16 blocks. Chunks can be claimed into a district, bought, sold, linked together, chunkloaded, taxed, and have their type changed.

Chunks can be set to many different Chunk Types:
§r§6NORMAL - §9Accessible by citizens of the municipality
§6PUBLIC - §9Accessible by anyone on the server
§6PRIVATE - §9Accessible by the owner and whitelisted people
§6DISTRICT -§9 Accessible by the district manager, municipality government, and the state government
§6MUNICIPALITY - §9Accessible by the municipality government and the state government
§6STATEOWNED - §9Accessible by the state government
§6STATEPUBLIC - §9Accessible by any member of the state

§rAll chunk commands use the /ck prefix, use /ck to see any commands not listed.

Claims the chunk you are standing in for a district
§2/ck claim <district-id>

§rReclaims the chunk to a different district
§2/ck reclaim <district-id>

§rGets information about the chunk you are in, this menu can be used to change aspects of the chunk
§2/ck info

§rBuys a chunk if it is for sale (Put it up for sale in the /ck info menu)
§2/ck buy

§rGets all possible chunk types
§2/ck types

Districts are made up of Chunks, and in turn Districts make up Municipalities. Districts can be bought, sold, taxed, and have the type changed.

Districts have attributes that determine what you can and can not do in them:
§6HOUSING
COMMERCE
INDUSTRY
CULTIVATION
EXPLOITATION
§r
Districts can be set to many different Districts Types:
§6WILDERNESS - §9No attributes
§6AGRICULTURAL - §9CULTIVATION
§6MINERAL - §9INDUSTRY, EXPLOITATION
§6VILLAGE - §9HOUSING, CULTIVATION
§6RESIDENTAL - §9HOUSING, COMMERCE
§6COMMERCIAL - §9COMMERCE, CULTIVATION
§6INDUSTRIAL - §9INDUSTRY
§6WASTELAND - §9EXPLOITATION
§6MUNICIPIAL - §9HOUSING COMMERCE
§r
All districts commands use the /dis prefix, use /dis to see any commands not listed.

Creates a new district. The amount of districts depends on how many chunks are in your border with everyone 32 chunks claimed unlocking a new district.
§2/dis create

§rGets information about the district you are in, this menu can be used to change aspects of the district
§2/dis info

Municipalities are made up of Districts, and in turn Municipalities make up States. Municipalities can be bought, sold, have citizens, tax those citizens, tax its chunks, and be the capital of a state.

Municipalities are what you're going to be using the most, and depending on the size determines the Title and how many chunks and districts your town can claim.

All municipalities commands use the /mun prefix, use /mun to see any commands not listed.

Create a new municipality. Costs $400
§2/mun create <name>

§rGets information about the municipality you are in, this menu can be used to change aspects of the municipality
§2/mun info

§rInvites the specified player to your current municipality
§2/mun invite <player>
§r
Joins the municipality you're standing in if it's open
§2/mun join

§rLeaves your municipality
§2/mun leave

States are made up of Municipalities. States can be bought, sold, have municipalities, take taxes from municipalities, and have a capital.

States are the highest layer currently available in states right now.

All municipalities commands use the /st prefix, use /st to see any commands not listed.

Creates a new State, §l§4§lMake sure you're standing in the municipality that you wish to be the capital!!
§2/st create <name>

§rGets information about the state you are in, this menu can be used to change aspects of the state. You can also invite additional municipalities to your state from this menu
§2/st info

§rNote: Support for States isn't fully fleshed out as of v0.6 so expect weird behavior with research syncing and things of that nature.

As of now the diplomacy system is fairly basic, but it will be updated as time goes on. But here is the basics of the current system:

Prints out all Municipalities whose mayors are online
§2/diplomacy online

§rDeclares war on the provided Municipality
§2/diplomacy declarewar <municipality-id>

§rMakes peace with the provided Municipality
§2/diplomacy peace <municipality-id>

§rDisplays who you are currently at war with
§2/diplomacy wars

§4As of now wars can only occur between municipalities, but state wars will come soon. For now you can just declare war on the capital of the state.

As a researcher you use town money to fund different research and development! Under the direction of the mayor, research technology for you nation.

Visit spawn or ask your mayor for an ATM to change your digital money to physical money for funding purposes!
This pack is pretty different from a normal pack, so this section will teach you the basics of creating your town and researching new technologies.

Begin your nations race for space with research and development into the stars.

This is a test of the new tech tree we plan to switch to for v0.7 so any feedback on this is greatly appreciated!
Research Books are new depreciated in favor of the new research system. These quests are only here to act as a control to compare to the new system to guage which one works better in practice.
Stuff's gotta get around somehow, and trains are cool. This will guide you through the Immersive Railroading mod and also unlock better trains as you funnel more money into your R&D!

All good towns need a mayor, and all good mayors need to spend those hard earned tax dollars. Appoint researchers to help you progress the tech tree. Since you're the mayor you decide who get's to help grow the town.
